ted with technological or regulatory shocks, and that a merger's success or failure was dependent upon the acquirer's thorough understanding of the target, its corporate culture, and its workforce and wage structures prior to acquisition. Sifting through a wealth of carefully gathered evidence, these papers capture the richness, the complexity, and the economic intangibles inherent in contemporary merger activity in a way that large-scale studies of mergers cannot.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aBarro, Jason R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalomiris, Charles W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCutler, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplan, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplan, Steven N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplan, Steven N., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKarceski, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKole, Stacey R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLehn, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLong, William F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMitchell, Mark L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRajan, Raghuram, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRavenscraft, David J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVolpin, Paolo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWruck, Karen H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZingales, Luigi, eco